## Fraud withdrawal review ā€” slice 4 (decision loop)

### Context
Completes the kinetic fraud-withdrawal review loop. The `review_withdrawal` ActionType
(slice 1's `flag_customer_high_risk` proof-of-seam has been retired) lets an agent propose
an approve/reject decision on a risky Withdrawal object; a human then either accepts it
(`approveAction`, 4-eyes enforced) or overrides it with their own decision (`overrideAction`,
mandatory reason). The `OVERRIDDEN` status is a new terminal state alongside `APPLIED`.
The `Withdrawal.decision` overlay field is live for read-back via GraphQL. Effect is still
`noop_log`; the real moneypool main-app API write-back and the real fraud-scoring agent are
deferred to later slices. Approver RBAC also remains deferred.

### Changes
1. `src/back/objects/actions/types/review_withdrawal.py` ā€” new `ReviewWithdrawal` ActionType:
   `id="review_withdrawal"`, `object_type="Withdrawal"`, `overlay_fields=["decision"]`,
   `requires_separate_approver=True`, `approval_policy=REQUIRES_APPROVAL`. Params:
   `withdrawal_id`, `recommendation` (approve|reject), `rationale`, `risk_assessment`.
   `apply()` composes a `decision` overlay value `{agent_recommendation, human_decision,
   agreed, decided_by, reason, decided_at}`. Effect: `noop_log`.
2. `src/back/objects/actions/base.py` ā€” `ActionStatus` gains `OVERRIDDEN`.
3. `src/back/objects/actions/service.py` ā€” `ActionService.override(action_id, approver,
   decision, reason, ctx)` validates non-empty reason + PROPOSED status, builds an augmented
   context with `decision_override`/`override_reason` in metadata, calls `_apply()` with
   `status="OVERRIDDEN"`, and drains effects post-commit.
4. `src/back/core/graphql/ResolverFactory.py` ā€” `make_review_withdrawal_resolver` (proposes
   via `reviewWithdrawal`); `make_override_resolver` (the `overrideAction` mutation).
5. `src/back/core/graphql/GraphQLSchemaBuilder.py` ā€” `_build_mutation` exposes
   `reviewWithdrawal`, `overrideAction`, `approveAction`, `rejectAction`. `Withdrawal.decision`
   read-back field attached via the overlay registry.
6. `src/agents/tools/actions.py` ā€” agent MCP tool re-pointed to `propose_review_withdrawal`
   (was `propose_flag_customer_high_risk`). `ACTION_TOOL_DEFINITIONS` and
   `ACTION_TOOL_HANDLERS` updated accordingly.
7. Retirement of `flag_customer_high_risk`: `src/back/objects/actions/types/flag_customer_high_risk.py`
   removed; its `flagCustomerHighRisk` mutation/resolver and associated tests removed.
8. `scripts/seed_fraud_withdrawals.sql` ā€” seed script for the fraud domain with sample
   Withdrawal objects for manual testing.
9. `docs/architecture.md`, `README.md` ā€” Kinetic Actions section updated: describes the
   fraud withdrawal review loop, `OVERRIDDEN` status, `overrideAction` mutation, and
   `Withdrawal.decision` overlay shape; removes `flag_customer_high_risk` / `riskFlag`
   references; lists deferred items (main-app write-back, fraud agent, RBAC).

