## Kinetic approve/reject mutations (slice 3)

### Context
Exposes the kinetic lifecycle's approve/reject over GraphQL so the full loop runs
in-browser (propose ā†’ a *different* user approves ā†’ riskFlag reflects it), with
per-ActionType segregation-of-duties (4-eyes). Foundational for AML-as-writer.
Approver authorization (RBAC) is a deferred follow-up.

### Changes
1. `src/back/objects/actions/action_type.py` ā€” `ActionType.requires_separate_approver:
   bool = False` (4-eyes opt-in per type). `types/flag_customer_high_risk.py` sets it True.
2. `src/back/objects/actions/audit.py` ā€” `AuditLog.get` now SELECTs + returns `actor`
   (the proposer) so approve can enforce 4-eyes.
3. `src/back/objects/actions/service.py` ā€” `approve` raises ActionError when
   `requires_separate_approver` and approver == proposer (inside the txn, before any
   write). `reject(action_id, approver, reason="")` records the reason in
   `action_log.after.rejected_reason`.
4. `src/back/core/graphql/ResolverFactory.py` ā€” `make_approve_resolver` /
   `make_reject_resolver` (annotated `-> ActionMutationResult`, catch ActionError ā†’
   `status="ERROR"` result). Inner closures named per-field (strawberry `create_type`
   dedupes by resolver `__name__` ā€” same-named closures would drop fields).
5. `src/back/core/graphql/GraphQLSchemaBuilder.py` ā€” `_build_mutation` adds
   `approveAction(actionId)` / `rejectAction(actionId, reason)` to the Mutation type.
6. `docs/architecture.md`, `README.md` ā€” document the two mutations + 4-eyes; note RBAC deferred.

### Modified / added files
- src/back/objects/actions/action_type.py, types/flag_customer_high_risk.py, audit.py, service.py
- src/back/core/graphql/ResolverFactory.py, GraphQLSchemaBuilder.py
- tests/units/actions/test_sod_decl.py (new), test_approve_reject_mutation.py (new), test_service.py (updated)
- docs/architecture.md, README.md

### Test result
- `uv run pytest tests/units` ā†’ 2143 passed, 11 skipped, 2 failed.
- The 2 failures are pre-existing + unrelated (`test_external_api.py::TestDomainVersions`,
  registry-not-configured offline). No new failures. Build-through-strawberry SDL check:
  approveAction/rejectAction/flagCustomerHighRisk all present.

