## Kinetic overlay read-back (slice 2)

### Context
Slice 2 completes the overlay read-back path introduced in the Kinetic Action Layer
(slice 1). ActionTypes now declare which overlay fields they produce; the registry
aggregates them; the GraphQL schema builder attaches a `JSON` scalar resolver per
`(object_type, prop)` pair directly onto the per-domain GraphQL object types
(e.g. `Customer.riskFlag`). The resolver queries `ontology_overlay` via the shared
`overlay_connect` callable threaded through the graphql route ā€” no extra connection
ownership. `flag_customer_high_risk` declares `riskFlag` on `Customer` as the live
proof-of-seam. Docs updated to reflect that read-back is no longer deferred.

### Changes
1. `src/back/objects/actions/action_type.py` ā€” `ActionType` gains class attr
   `overlay_fields: list[str] = []` (property names it writes on its `object_type`).
   `src/back/objects/actions/types/flag_customer_high_risk.py` sets
   `overlay_fields = ["riskFlag"]`.
2. `src/back/objects/actions/registry.py` ā€” `ActionRegistry.overlay_fields_by_type()`
   aggregates declared property names across all registered types, returning
   `dict[str, set[str]]` keyed by object type name (types with no fields omitted).
3. `src/back/core/graphql/ResolverFactory.py` ā€” `make_overlay_field_resolver`'s inner
   resolver is annotated `-> Optional[JSON]` (so strawberry can build the field) and
   wrapped in an error-isolating try/except (a read failure logs + returns `None`,
   never breaks the query). Added `from strawberry.scalars import JSON`.
4. `src/back/core/graphql/GraphQLSchemaBuilder.py` ā€” `_add_overlay_fields` iterates
   `overlay_fields_by_type()`, finds the matching plain Python class, and injects an
   `Optional[JSON]` `strawberry.field` resolver per prop BEFORE `_apply_strawberry_types`
   freezes it. `overlay_connect` + `domain` are threaded through `build_for_domain` ā†’
   `_build`; the schema cache key gains a `-o` suffix when overlays are attached.
5. `src/back/fastapi/graphql_routes.py` ā€” `_get_schema_and_context` passes the same
   pooled `connect` callable (already built for the mutation factories) as
   `overlay_connect` on the Lakebase-reachable path; query-only paths pass `None`.
6. `docs/architecture.md` ā€” Kinetic Actions "Entry points" section updated: read-back
   is live (describes `overlay_fields`, registry aggregation, `_add_overlay_fields`,
   and resolver threading). The slice-1 follow-up bullet deferring the riskFlag field
   is removed. Two remaining follow-ups retained (real Effect connectors;
   ontology-defined Action Types).
7. `README.md` ā€” Kinetic Actions blurb updated to note overlay read-back is live.

