## Multi-client deploy: CLIENT= wrapper + onboarding runbook

### Context
OntoBricks is operated per-client (multi-tenant); moneypool is the first client.
This makes client selection a first-class deploy flag and documents the full
new-client onboarding path (provision Lakebase ā†’ UC schema/volume ā†’ per-client
config ā†’ deploy dev-lakebase ā†’ bind Postgres in UI ā†’ initialize registry).

### Changes
1. `Makefile` ā€” `CONFIG` is now client-aware:
   `CONFIG := scripts/deploy.config$(if $(strip $(CLIENT)),.$(strip $(CLIENT)),).sh`.
   Added `CLIENT ?=` + `export CLIENT` so every config-sourcing target
   (deploy, render-app-yaml, bootstrap-perms, bootstrap-lakebase, bundle-validate,
   deploy-check) and the invoked `scripts/deploy.sh` all resolve the same
   per-client config. Updated the help text to document `CLIENT=<name>`.
2. `scripts/deploy.sh` ā€” config loading honors `CLIENT`: selects
   `scripts/deploy.config.<CLIENT>.sh` when set (else the default sandbox config),
   still allows an explicit `CONFIG_FILE` override, and prints a helpful error
   pointing at the expected per-client config when it is missing. Default
   (no CLIENT) behavior is unchanged.
3. `docs/client-onboarding.md` ā€” new runbook: 11 steps from auth ā†’ Lakebase
   provisioning ā†’ UC schema/volume ā†’ per-client config ā†’ first deploy (incl. the
   "app already exists" bind fix) ā†’ UI Postgres binding + reading back the resource
   path ā†’ registry initialize ā†’ optional SP grants ā†’ verification ā†’ optional LLM
   auto-pipeline. Plus an everyday `make ... CLIENT=<client>` quick reference.

